      "message": "Yeah, Clang just requires -msse2 explicitly, and uses the flag -m32 to switch to a 32-bit target instead of requiring you to run a different binary for the same effect.\n\nThere is flag similar to -msse2 and -mfpmath\u003dsse that we might be able to use instead, /arch:SSE2.  We might not be passing it to MSVC right now (because that is its default), and we\u0027d have to pass the opposite /arch:IA32 to turn those features off there.  It should be harmless to pass /arch:SSE2 on all Windows builds?",
